.TH RMBG "1" "May 2026" "rmbg 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rmbg \- remove image backgrounds using ImageMagick
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rmbg
[\fIfile\fR|\fIfolder\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Removes solid color backgrounds from images using ImageMagick.
Works with PNG, JPG, JPEG, GIF, and ICNS files.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-prefix\fR \fIPREFIX\fR
.RS
Add prefix to output filename (e.g., 'clean_')
.RE
.PP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-suffix\fR \fISUFFIX\fR
.RS
Add suffix to output (default: '_clean')
.RE
.PP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-replace\fR
.RS
Replace original file
.RE
.PP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-open\fR
.RS
Open result after processing
.RE
.PP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-fuzz\fR \fIPERCENT\fR
.RS
Fuzz percentage for color matching (default: 15)
.RE
.PP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
.RS
Recursively process subfolders
.RE
.PP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-background\fR \fICOLOR\fR
.RS
Background color: auto (default), black, white, or hex code
.RE
.PP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-antialias\fR
.RS
Smooth/anti-alias the output edges
.RE
.PP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-desaturate\fR
.RS
Convert output logo to grayscale (kills colored halos)
.RE
.PP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-white\fR
.RS
Remove white background
.RE
.PP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-match\fR \fIPATTERN\fR
.RS
Only process files matching pattern (e.g., 'logo')
.RE
.PP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.RS
Show processing info
.RE
.PP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS
Show help message
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Remove black background from single image:
.RS
.B rmbg image.png
.RE
.PP
Remove white background from folder (recursive):
.RS
.B rmbg folder/ \-R \-w
.RE
.PP
Only process files with 'logo' in name:
.RS
.B rmbg folder/ \-R \-m "logo"
.RE
.PP
Replace originals with white background:
.RS
.B rmbg folder/ \-r \-w
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR convert (1),
.BR identify (1)